{"id": "EUVD-2025-5981", "enisaUuid": "f8421c0d-8cbe-3a1a-afe5-e5fed59c6f2c", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nptp: vmclock: Set driver data before its usage\n\nIf vmclock_ptp_register() fails during probing, vmclock_remove() is\ncalled to clean up the ptp clock and misc device.\nIt uses dev_get_drvdata() to access the vmclock state.\nHowever the driver data is not yet set at this point.\n\nAssign the driver data earlier.", "datePublished": "2025-02-27T21:32:17", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-28T03:30:13", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-21822", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6dbd8b91a065d1d8001446a28e72cd140f9acef0", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f7d07cd4f77d77f366c8ffbb8ba8b61f614e5fce"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-21822", "GHSA-5jx9-3p7f-55g3"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.04, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0da70097-4a74-3fd8-b1b1-634971d0502b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "20503272422693d793b84f88bf23fe4e955d3a33 <f7d07cd4f77d77f366c8ffbb8ba8b61f614e5fce"}, {"id": "156ec8b3-e5ee-34a5-8daf-5b9cdb2fa726", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.13.4"}, {"id": "6f2835cd-7a15-3c53-b6e3-757224da59e9", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "9ab8b8c5-5747-3442-96f8-0607432fe844", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "20503272422693d793b84f88bf23fe4e955d3a33 <6dbd8b91a065d1d8001446a28e72cd140f9acef0"}, {"id": "b39b0f8b-fb80-304a-b1cb-0c614e550fa3", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.13"}, {"id": "badcd2ea-a8fc-332d-a69e-a5e8b104253a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.14"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "62d2753e-908f-3513-bb8f-0f2bfe42ebe2", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}